0.text: • Cover the cage or barrel with coconut fronds or suitable covering material and maintain the moisture inside. • Finally, collect produced compost from the bottom of the cage or barrel. • Add water regularly. • Then, fill in the cage or barrel with different raw materials such as green leaves, weeds, banana leaves and trunks, salvinia, sawdust, vegetable peels, crop waste and animal waste. • Add inoculants to increase the decomposition of raw materials.
